						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone lying in the compound of the Baraguṇḍi house.</p>						

						<p>Gūvala.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the king Gōvala, apparently of the Goa Kadamba family, and describes the loyalty and valour of a warrior who seems to have died in a fight. The inscription is much damaged, the details being lost.</p>						

						</summary>
